<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF486AF7F82C942517F5B850" pageId="179" pageNumber="941" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF486AF7F82C942517F5B850" blockId="179.[1998,2595,557,984]" pageId="179" pageNumber="941">
Subgenus Pizonyx; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF486AF7F72094251748B9AF" authorityName="E. Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1806" box="[2268,2376,636,669]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="179" pageNumber="941" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albescens">albescens</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF486AF7F82C94FA1622B9F6" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[2000,2082,675,708]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="179" pageNumber="941" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
dinelliiwas considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF486AF7F82C948A1636B9DE" authorityName="I. Geoffroy" authorityYear="1824" box="[2000,2102,723,748]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="179" pageNumber="941" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="levis">M. levis</taxonomicName>
, but taxonomic reviews confirmed its status as a distinct specific. Records for southern 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF486AF7F7A0954016AAB808" box="[2140,2218,793,826]" name="Brazil" pageId="179" pageNumber="941">Brazil</collectingCountry>
were invalidated because specimens were 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF486AF7F74D9518174CB850" authorityName="E. Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1806" box="[2225,2380,833,866]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="179" pageNumber="941" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albescens">M. albescens</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
